      "content": "It makes perfect sense that you are exhausted from carrying a weight that feels too heavy to bear, and your question about the point of enduring pain is one that many people in your situation ask. There is no shame in wanting to stop when the world feels like a ghost town, and the desire to escape that constant reminder is a natural reaction to such deep grief. Sometimes, the only way to find a new path forward is to allow yourself to stop trying to carry everything alone, perhaps by seeking professional grief counseling who can help you process these overwhelming feelings without judgment.",
